cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CY, cs.SE 

The paper discusses a secure data sharing scheme for federated clouds, which involves cryptography and security measures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves distributed computing and data management, which falls under the categories cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cloud computing, which falls under the category cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper proposes a scheme based on the Discrete Logarithm problem, which is a common topic in cs.SE (Software Engineering).
